title: Real Life Cooking

episodes.title: Love Your Leftovers: Chicken & Black Bean Enchiladas
episodes.summary: Looking for leftover redemption? Follow Katie and Robin as they transform common leftover foods, such as roasted chicken, steak and rice, into a cheesy, flavor-packed dish.

episodes.title: Love Your Leftovers: Steak Tortilla Soup
episodes.summary: Robin talks Katie through her go-to recipe for leftover steak, made with a few pantry staples such as beef broth, Mexican spices and beans.

episodes.title: Slow Cookin for the Big Game: Chile con Queso
episodes.summary: In preparation for football-sized appetites, Robin and Katie tackle the slow cooker with a simple homemade dip that calls for, you guessed it, cheese, and more cheese.

episodes.title: Slow Cookin for the Big Game: Beef, Beer & BBQ Stew
episodes.summary: After a brief halftime, Katie shows Robin her game-winning beef stew recipe, sharing tips for slow-cooker success along the way.

episodes.title: Bake Sale: One-Pot Fudgy Brownies
episodes.summary: What to make for that bake sale you just found out about? Robin and Katie tackle this classic dilemma with 15-minute from-scratch brownies that will bring in the dough.

episodes.title: Bake Sale: Pumpkin Spice Donut Holes
episodes.summary: Discover the perfect bite-sized treats for bake sales and beyond! Katie shares her signature recipe for baked pumpkin donut holes with cinnamon sugar.

episodes.title: Shortcuts: Apricot-Teriyaki Meatballs
episodes.summary: Robin serves up her favorite shortcut recipe for flavor-packed meals in under 30 minutes, as well as time-saving tips along the way.

episodes.title: Shortcuts: Beefy-Cheesy Macaroni
episodes.summary: Katie gives shortcut tips to make a crave-worthy one-pot pasta dish perfect for weeknight dinners.

episodes.title: Chickened Out: Parmesan Chicken Pops With Marinara
episodes.summary: Katie and Robin shake up their chicken dinner routine with a go-to recipe that you can make in 30 minutes or less. Kids will love it!

episodes.title: Chickened Out: Chicken in Mustard
episodes.summary: Gussy up some quick-cooking chicken cutlets  with an easy yet sophisticated pan sauce. Robin and Katie show you how to add this elegant dish to your weeknight repertoire.

summary: Finally, a cooking show about real life, where real problems pop up and real mistakes happen. In this Craftsy Original series, at-home cooks Robin Miller and Katie Workman tackle common kitchen conundrums with simple solutions that get dinner on the table amidst a busy schedule — and dish up some laughs along the way.

relatedPlaylists.title: Vegetables for Every Season

episodes.title: Vegetables for Every Season: Spring Asparagus
episodes.summary: Green is back in the garden, and Nicki will highlight her favorite Spring vegetables with a special focus on asparagus. She'll show you a new way to prep asparagus for an unforgettable Spaghetti with Shaved Asparagus & Mint Pesto and then walk you through a bright and crisp Asparagus & Quinoa Salad loaded with peas, radishes, fennel, golden raisins and almonds.

chapters.name: Spaghetti With Shaved Asparagus & Mint Pesto

episodes.title: Vegetables for Every Season: Spring Greens
episodes.summary: Staying in the spring, Nicki shares her filling Fingerling Potato & Greens Hash that's perfect for any time of day. Then you'll learn how to make her Coconut Chard Gratin, which is both creamy and dairy-free.

chapters.name: New Potato & Greens Hash With Cheddar Cheese

episodes.title: Vegetables for Every Season: Summer Tomatoes
episodes.summary: If you wait all year for sweet, juicy summer tomatoes, Nicki will show you how to showcase their goodness with a Golden Tomato & Corn Gazpacho and Grilled Panzanella Salad. Also, learn her techniques for a No­Cook Tomato Sauce with Toasted Almonds.

episodes.title: Vegetables for Every Season: Summer Squash
episodes.summary: Summer is when produce is at its most abundant. Nicki shares her strategies for dealing with the bounty of squash with tender Zucchini Cakes with Garlic Yogurt and a stunning Summer Squash Gratin.

episodes.title: Fall & Winter: Root Vegetables & Winter Squash
episodes.summary: When cold weather sets in, it's easy to get bored with the vegetables on your plate. Nicki livens up your fall and winter vegetables with modern takes on root vegetables and winter squash. Learn her complex Curried Sweet Potato Soup Bowls with Frizzled Kale, Apples & Peanuts and then serve up spicy Spaghetti Squash, Black Bean & Chard Tacos with Avocado, Radishes and Creamy Chipotle Sauce.

chapters.name: Spaghetti Squash Tacos With Creamy Chipotle Sauce

episodes.title: Fall & Winter: Cruciferous Vegetables
episodes.summary: Cruciferous vegetables are crunchy and bright in Nicki's kitchen. Cook her Caramelized Brussels Sprouts & Mushrooms with Honey­Garlic Balsamic Vinaigrette & Fried Shallots and Creamy Cauliflower Soup with Almond ­Caper­Cauliflower Salsa and change the way your guests perspectives on these fall and winter staples.

chapters.name: Caramelized Brussels Sprouts With Fried Shallots
Creamy Cauliflower Soup With Almond-Caper Salsa

episodes.title: Year-Round Recipes
episodes.summary: Throughout the class, Nicki has shown you techniques to highlight the seasonal bounty. Here she shares some of her favorite techniques that can be used to showcase ingredients in any season. Her Thai red curry, frittata, fried rice, and flatbread will be your secret weapons year round.

relatedPlaylists.summary: Cook your favorite seasonal veggies in new, inspiring ways.

relatedPlaylists.title: One-Pot Cooking

episodes.title: Nonstick-Skillet Dishes
episodes.summary: Meet Ryan Scott and Dylan Dreyer! Ryan begins class by sharing his go-to nonstick pan. Then he shows you how to build a one-pan turkey lasagna using no-boil noodles, plus his family's favorite recipe for pork larb, a flavor-packed family-style dish that's served in lettuce cups.

chapters.name: Turkey Lasagna With Goat Cheese, Basil & Parmesan

episodes.title: Cast-Iron Pan Meals
episodes.summary: Bring home bold steakhouse flavor, even on a busy weeknight! Here, Ryan and Dylan use a cast-iron skillet to make the perfect steak with a sautéed mushroom pan sauce and basil compound butter. Afterwards, learn to make a quick and tasty pineapple upside-down cake using Ryan's secret ingredient.

chapters.name: Resting the Meat & Making Mushroom Cream Sauce

episodes.title: Multi-Cooker Dinners
episodes.summary: Whether you own a slow cooker, pressure cooker or one that does it all, find out how to maximize it with two mouthwatering recipes. First, see how to make a knockout brisket chili. Then watch as Ryan prepares his family's favorite slow cooker recipe: corn, cheddar and ham pudding with velvety, luscious texture.

chapters.name: Making the Spice Mix & Cutting the Brisket
Building Flavor in the Slow Cooker
Creamed Corn, Cheddar Cheese & Ham Pudding

episodes.title: Sheet-Pan Cooking
episodes.summary: Ryan and Dylan use a sheet pan to make spatchcock roasted chicken with cauliflower, olives and salsa verde. After that, Ryan tackles a chicken and walnut pesto sheet pan pizza that will serve any crowd. He even shares a few smart pizza-making tricks to help you along the way.

chapters.name: Spatchcock Chicken With Roasted Vegetables & Salsa

episodes.title: Packet Cooking
episodes.summary: Using parchment paper or foil packets is an elegant (and easy!) way to make one-pot meals that are healthy and delicious. Follow along as Ryan and Dylan prepare salmon in a parchment pouch layered with brown rice, asparagus and lemon. Then Ryan shows you how to make his Hawaiian chicken steamed in a foil packet with pineapple and homemade teriyaki sauce.

episodes.title: Make-Ahead One-Pot Meals
episodes.summary: It always helps to have a few make-ahead dishes in your repertoire, especially if you're on a tight schedule. In this final lesson, Ryan teaches you how to make a veggie-packed Mediterranean egg bake that's perfect for any time of the day, and overnight French toast with creamy custard filling. Plus get tips on caramelizing sugar with a kitchen blowtorch!

relatedPlaylists.summary: Master more than 10 tasty one-pot recipes that are simple enough for busy weeknights and special enough for guests. As seen on the TODAY Show's TODAY Food segment!

relatedPlaylists.title: One-Dish Meals Made New

episodes.title: Overview & Shove-It-in-the-Oven Stews
episodes.summary: Meet chef Pam Anderson, a New York Times best-selling cookbook author and AARP's food expert. Learn more about the simple one-dish meals you'll make in this class, then dive right into preparing two of Pam's "shove-it-in-the-oven stews": a hearty cassoulet with beans and sausage, and a creamy chicken-and-vegetable stew. These one-dish recipes are sure to be a delicious addition to your weeknight repertoire.

episodes.title: Oven-Roasted Fish & Vegetables
episodes.summary: With a single sheet pan you can prepare an entire meal of roasted fish and vegetables! Pam discusses the types of fish to use and how to roast the fish alongside fingerling potatoes and green vegetables such as green beans, spinach and asparagus. She provides lots of ideas for drizzles and simple sauces to go with the fish and vegetables, turning them into elegant meals that can be doubled to feed up to eight appreciative guests!

episodes.title: Paella
episodes.summary: If you thought Spanish paella was only for special occasions, think again! Pam shares her techniques for preparing this rice-based dish, chock-full of chicken, sausage and seafood. You don't need a paella pan; Pam shows you how to make this flavorful dish in a large skillet or Dutch oven! She also gives tips for preparing components of the dish ahead of time.

episodes.title: Braised Lamb Shanks
episodes.summary: Pam takes the guesswork out of preparing delectable, fall-off-the-bone lamb shanks, and shows you how to do it quickly with the help of a hot oven and aluminum foil. You'll build up a flavor base with onion, carrots and celery before braising the shanks, then add hearty white beans to complete the dish. If you love lamb, this is the dinner for you!

episodes.title: Stuffed Beef Tenderloin
episodes.summary: Celebrate any special occasion with Pam's stuffed beef tenderloin, which is out of this world! She discusses what to look for when buying this pricey cut, and shows you how to butterfly it for stuffing with blue cheese and breadcrumbs. Roast the beef in the same pan (and at the same time!) as a barley and mushroom pilaf, and use the pan drippings to make a rich port wine sauce to complete the festive meal.

episodes.title: Chicken Pot Pie
episodes.summary: There's nothing as comforting as chicken pot pie, and it couldn't be easier with Pam's technique for preparing it. Use leeks and apples as Pam does, or go the traditional route with peas and carrots. It's a weeknight-friendly recipe when you make a speedy white sauce and use rotisserie chicken, then top your pie with a quick drop biscuit dough or a store-bought pie crust. You can even divide the recipe in two and make a pot pie to freeze for later!

episodes.title: Lasagna
episodes.summary: Pam's familiar-yet-special lasagna with mushrooms and caramelized onions will please everyone at your table. Pam shows you her tricks for working with no-boil noodles, quickly caramelizing onions, and shares another delicious variation on her speedy white sauce before demonstrating her simple layering technique. The lasagna bakes up creamy, cheesy and incredibly delicious; it might just become your new favorite!

relatedPlaylists.summary: Learn timesaving techniques and family-friendly recipes for one-dish meals you'll crave, from chicken pot pie to blue cheese-stuffed beef tenderloin and more!
